<br>
so what we do know. <br>
<br>
It works best in zones where there is already low agro. meaning that you can run past most mobs without agroing them. or you can run up to the mob and back away without getting agro.<br>
<br>
It causes less agro then attacking the mob and trying to pull that way.<br>
<br>
Agro does not seem to pass from the mob you beg pulled, to other mobs around him when beg is used.<br>
<br>
it helps to have sow on but is not needed.<br>
<br>
What we dont know.<br>
<br>
If beg pulling only works in zones that have merchants (mainly cause im lazy) but alot of zones that dont have merchants, mobs rarly have low agro. I need to test this in the 1st floor of ssra at the zone in. mobs have low agro and you can run past some without agroing.<br>
<br>
Note: I remember begging from a charmed mob in SolB efreeti camp long before they putin the ragefire merchant/npc. so begging might work in certain non merchant zones.<br>
<br>
I still have not come up with a list of zones that beg puling works in.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Now as to why I am posting this and continuing to folow up on it. Beg is great for pulling in certain situations. and you can pull equaly good in zones where it works, as good as a monk using FD. if this works in enough zones it will add to our pulling abilities and lessen our dependence on FD pullers.<br>
<br>
How to Beg pull. (YOU NEED TO GET BEG OFF BEFORE THE MOB AGROS YOU VIA RANGE) This needs to be done in a smooth motion. Run up and when you are close enough press beg. now you need to turn around as quick as you can. turn before you beg if possible. if you agro the mob and he attacks you and you reposte you will get regular agro and not beg agro. this is bad.<br>
<br>
Beg pulling Scribe and Hunter through full spawn (Minus Dain). Invis up to scribe room. take off invis. run up turn around and press beg. run out of the room hugging the wall that is farthest away from the royal guards. run down to the steps. wait for scribe to catch up to you (he might start to cast) run down to the next level and check for roamers when its clear run down to the bottom level. check and wait for roamers. run and open the gate and make a run for the zone. NOTE: it makes it easier if you have someone at the gate opening it for you.<br>
<br>
<br>
Just though I would post this to keep my fellow warriors abreast of new pulling techs. it works in other zones i just have to keep better notes. hehe<br>
<br>
Finaly Begpulling is not ment to be used in every situation only those situations where pulling with range or attack will cause adds. ie: past the royals in ice well.<br>
