Probably isn't beg causing the aggro if the puller is already KOS- try the same thing but spam /con instead.  Basically, the &quot;I know you are there and I hate you&quot; frenzy aggro radius is *sometimes* bigger than the &quot;I hate you but I don't see you yet, get any closer and I will tho&quot; radius.  Using /con, targeting, begging, etc all &quot;tell&quot; the mob you are there.  And since it's &quot;spontaneous&quot; frenzy as opposed to attack aggro, the mob doesn't shout for help, so you (sometimes) get them solo.<br>
<br>
In programmerspeak, I'd say that the act of /con-ing, targeting, etc. all initialize the mob's hate list and/or force an aggro check, probably both.  Spamming /con increases the frequency of the checks, etc.<br>
<br>
I did a write up on the monkly business board awhile ago on &quot;/con pulling&quot;.  It's easiest to see with a level 60 in someplace like fungus grove or sol b imps (i.e. on dk blue mobs- the frenzy radii seem to be level related etc.).  For instance, in FG you can sit at a certain distance from a shroom patch basically forever and the npcs won't aggro.  But if you target one, and perhaps start spamming /con, it'll frenzy and attack, usually solo.  Very repeatable, very nice for splitting spawns. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
